 I agree; aggro is the entire parties responsibility. <br>
<br>
If ye are doing something that is causing ye to aggro the mob and drain the healers' mana  *especially in a timed dungeon*; then whatever it is you are doing should cease. <br>
<br>
 The lightest heals mana-wise at elevated seasons, are very long cast  * c-heal *. The quicker ones that are often required on an 'aggro-tag' pull are very, very expensive.  <br>
<br>
 especially group complete heals.  <br>
<br>
 If ye find yourself as secondary tank even, and are constantly taking aggro, thus needing those incessant 'patch-heals' from the cleric; ye should find out what is going wrong. <br>
<br>
 Those patch heals are likely costing more to keep ye healthy than it is to keep the mains' HP at ready. <br>
<br>
 A flurry of attacks on the main while I am in the middle of healing a secondary for the ump-teenth-millionth time is a sure way to end a life.<br>
<br>
and I only get one 100% rezz every eighteen hour all              <br>
